docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, July 17. -- There are indications that the early reflux of transatlantic travel will be very strong. Already preferred accommodations on popular steamships have all been engaged up to Oct. 1.

headline.main: REFLUX OF TRAVEL FROM LONDON IS ON; Westward Steamers Show Heavy Bookings and Height of Hotel Season Is Past. BAD WEATHER A FACTOR Frederick Townsend Martin to Give a Smart Luncheon -- Countess Szechenyi Returning to Hungary.
